Ta có $\vert x-2 \vert = \begin{cases}
x-2 \textrm{ khi } x\geq 2\\
2-x \textrm{ khi } x\leq 2
\end{cases}$$\\$
Do đó 
\begin{align*}
\displaystyle\int\limits_1^5\dfrac{2\vert x-2 \vert +1}{x}\mathrm{\, d}x &=\int\limits_1^2\dfrac{2(2-x)+1}{x}\mathrm{\, d}x+\int\limits_2^5\dfrac{2(x-2)+1}{x}\mathrm{\, d}x=\int\limits_1^2\left (\dfrac{5}{x}-2\right )\mathrm{\, d}x+\int\limits_2^5\left (2-\dfrac{3}{x}\right )\mathrm{\, d}x \\
&=\left (5\ln \vert x\vert -2x\right )\bigg |_1^2+\left (2x-3\ln \vert x\vert \right )\bigg |_2^5=4+8\ln 2-3\ln 5
\end{align*} 
Vậy $a+b=5$.

Đặt $t=3-x\Rightarrow  \begin{cases}
-\mathrm{d}t=\mathrm{d}x\\ x=3-t \end{cases}\Rightarrow K=-\displaystyle\int\limits_{3}^{0}\dfrac{\mathrm{d}t}{1+f(3-t)}=\displaystyle\int\limits_{0}^{3}\dfrac{\mathrm{d}x}{1+f(3-x)} $;$\\$
Vậy $2K= \displaystyle\int\limits_{0}^{3}\Bigg[\dfrac{1}{1+f(x)}+\dfrac{1}{1+f(3-x)}\Bigg]\mathrm{d}x=3\Leftrightarrow K=\dfrac{3}{2}.$
